// ============================================================================
// bc-shop Implementer->Reviewer loop + GATED work_done, as a fabro DOT workflow.
// Slice 2 Leg 1 -> Slice 3 Leg B (runtime) -> Slice 5 HARDEN (epic lead-6k1r).
// Faithfully realizes 01b-target-loop-workdone.md section 2. Branch fabro-spike.
// SPIKE / THROWAWAY.
//
// ========================= SLICE 5 HARDEN — NO-NODE-COLLAPSE (this leg) =======
// Slice 4 GOAL was PARTIAL: the 'prime' node was a general read-write AGENT that
// carried the graph goal and ran the ENTIRE pipeline itself (consumed inbox,
// wrote test(red)+feat(green), pushed, ran bc-emit) inside ONE stage — the
// downstream loop nodes never ran (findings 04-goal-demo.md). ROOT CAUSE: a
// fabro command node is a general agent whose scope/decomposition/sole-emit are
// ADVISORY, not enforced. FIX (this leg): every NON-JUDGMENT node is now a
// NATIVE `script=` deterministic step (shape=parallelogram) — NO LLM agency, it
// physically cannot run away — and only genuine JUDGMENT steps stay agents.
//
//  NATIVE (script=, no LLM): prime health arm armed worktree redgate integ
//    wdg_r wdg_f emit_r emit_f emit_clar emit_blk reported halt.
//  AGENT (judgment only): classify suff plan impl impl_f review.
//
// STRUCTURAL ENFORCEMENT (the anti-collapse guarantee): every STATE-CHANGING
//   action — draining the inbox, integrating to main, the work-done GATE, and
//   emitting work_done via bc-emit — is a NATIVE script node with no LLM. The
//   judgment agents can ONLY route (emit a preferred_next_label directive) and
//   write within their lane; they can NOT emit work_done, integrate, or bypass a
//   gate, because those nodes are deterministic and sit between every agent and
//   the mailbox. emit_r (bc-emit, status=complete) is the SOLE work_done emitter
//   on the scenario path and is reachable ONLY via review->signoff->wdg_r->pass,
//   all of wdg_r/emit_r being native. A rogue/mis-signalling reviewer therefore
//   still cannot emit a false complete: wdg_r (native) re-runs the 3 checks and
//   the bc-emit wrapper re-runs the gate again.
//
// ========================= ENV-OVERLAY INPUT-INTO-SCRIPT (Slice 5, PROVEN) ====
// Slice 3 pinned that `{{ inputs.NAME }}` ([run.inputs] + -I) is NOT visible in
// `script=` nor as sandbox env. Slice 5 PROVED the WORKAROUND: the GLOBAL
// `[run.environment.env]` overlay (the same channel that delivered HTTPS_PROXY/CA
// to the shim leg) DOES reach the NATIVE command sandbox. Probe (host server
// 127.0.0.1:32276, run 01KWDVPMCZA2M8N8J5MGRF6KCM): a `shape=parallelogram`
// node with `script="echo PROBE_BC=[$BC_NAME] PROBE_WID=[$WORK_ID]"` printed
// `PROBE_BC=[shopsystem-example] PROBE_WID=[lead-envprobe1]` with BC_NAME/WORK_ID
// declared under `[run.environment.env]`. => WORK_ID/BC_NAME-parameterized GATE
// and EMIT nodes are now NATIVE `script=` reading `$BC_NAME`/`$WORK_ID` from env.
// NO node needs to stay an agent merely to interpolate a run input. (Agents that
// still want the values in their PROMPT text use `{{ inputs.NAME }}`; both
// channels are declared in workflow.toml and kept in sync.)
//
// NATIVE MULTI-BRANCH (Slice 5, PROVEN NEGATIVE): a native node emitting
//   `{"preferred_next_label":"message"}` on stdout is NOT honored — the run
//   ignored it and took the other labelled edge (probe DirProbe). A native node
//   has EXACTLY two outcomes: exit 0 => `succeeded`, nonzero => `failed`. It can
//   NOT self-route among several success labels. => any deterministic 2-way
//   fork is modelled as a native SUCCESS edge (uncond) + a `condition=` edge:
//   `arm` is therefore SPLIT into `arm` (drain, error=>halt) then `armed`
//   (message-present => succeeded => classify; empty inbox => failed => done idle).
//
// ========================= RUNTIME MECHANICS (Slice 3 Leg B, still in force) ===
// fabro v0.254.0.
//  (U2/AC2) NATIVE command node = `shape=parallelogram, script="<cmd>"`. NO LLM;
//    exit 0 => outcome `succeeded`, nonzero => `failed`. `script=` is LITERAL
//    (no minijinja) but DOES inherit the `[run.environment.env]` overlay (above).
//    AGENT node = `shape=box/ellipse, class="..."` with a `prompt=`; its stage
//    outcome is the AGENT's, not a shell exit code.
//  (U1/AC4) FAIL-CLOSED TERMINAL. A native node whose `script` exits nonzero and
//    has NO outgoing edge yields run=FAILED ("stage failed with no outgoing fail
//    edge"). => `halt` is a native `script="...; exit 1"` SINK.
//  (ROUTING) transitions cascade: (1) `condition=` edges; (2) an AGENT's
//    `{"preferred_next_label":"<L>"}` directive vs edge `label=`; (3)
//    suggested_next_ids; (4) unconditional fallback (a labelled edge is eligible
//    and preferred over an unlabeled one). `label=` alone does NOT route — the
//    AGENT prompt MUST emit the directive; a native node can NOT emit one.
//  (PROVEN-SAFE PATTERN) single-success node: `node -> success` (UNCONDITIONAL,
//    no label) + `node -> fail [condition="outcome=failed"]`. Multi-branch AGENT
//    node: labelled directive-routed branches + one `condition="outcome=failed"`
//    catch.
//
// CREDENTIALS: no node reads a real secret. Every node inherits HTTPS_PROXY ->
//   agent-vault via the same `[run.environment.env]` overlay; fabro's vault holds
//   only __PLACEHOLDER__. LLM calls reach Anthropic through the
//   anthropic-oauth-shim (see anthropic-oauth-shim/).
// ============================================================================
digraph BcShopLoop {
    graph [
        goal="Recreate the bc-shop Implementer->Reviewer loop for BC {{ inputs.BC_NAME }} / work {{ inputs.WORK_ID }} and emit a GATED work_done via shop-msg/bc-emit. Reviewer is the SOLE work_done emitter on the scenario path. HARD RULE: a FAILED node must never advance to the SUCCEEDED terminal; every fallible node carries an explicit unconditional failsafe edge to halt (infra) or emit_blk (deliverable). STRUCTURAL RULE: every state-changing action (inbox drain, integrate, work-done gate, bc-emit) is a NATIVE non-LLM script node; agents may ONLY judge and route."
        model_stylesheet="* { model: claude-haiku-4-5 } .coding { model: claude-sonnet-4-5 } .review { model: claude-sonnet-4-5 }"
        rankdir=TB
        fallback_retry_target="halt"
    ]

    // ---------- terminals ---------------------------------------------------
    // `done` = the single Msquare SUCCEEDED terminal.
    // `halt` = NATIVE command sink (script exits 1, NO outgoing edge) => FAILED.
    // `reported` = NATIVE command node (exit 0) marking a correct non-failure
    //          reporting end, then passes through to `done` (SUCCEEDED).
    start    [shape=Mdiamond, label="Start"]
    done     [shape=Msquare,  label="Exit: SUCCEEDED\n(work_done complete emitted, or idle-empty)"]
    reported [shape=parallelogram,
              label="REPORTED",
              script="echo 'REPORTED: a clarify OR work_done(blocked) was already emitted upstream; correct non-failure reporting end'; exit 0"]
    halt     [shape=parallelogram,
              label="HALTED / FAILED (terminal sink)",
              script="echo 'HALT/FAILED: session-start infra failure (prime/health/arm) or retry-exhausted emit collision; NO role work emitted'; exit 1"]

    // ---------- session start (NATIVE script nodes; $BC_NAME/$WORK_ID from the
    //            [run.environment.env] overlay -- NO LLM, cannot run the loop) --
    prime    [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=3,
              label="prime", prompt_file="nodes/bc-router.md",
              script="set -e; shop-msg prime --bc \"$BC_NAME\"; bd prime"]
    health   [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=2,
              label="work-tracker health gate", prompt_file="nodes/bc-router.md",
              script="set -e; bd ready >/dev/null 2>&1; shop-msg pending inbox --bc \"$BC_NAME\" >/dev/null 2>&1"]
    arm      [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true,
              label="arm: drain inbox (reachability)", prompt_file="nodes/bc-router.md",
              script="shop-msg pending inbox --bc \"$BC_NAME\" > \"/tmp/fabro_pending_${WORK_ID}.txt\" 2>&1"]
    armed    [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true,
              label="armed: message present? read it", prompt_file="nodes/bc-router.md",
              script="n=$(shop-msg pending inbox --bc \"$BC_NAME\" 2>/dev/null | grep -c \"$WORK_ID\"); if [ \"${n:-0}\" -ge 1 ]; then shop-msg read inbox --bc \"$BC_NAME\" --work-id \"$WORK_ID\"; exit 0; else echo 'inbox empty for this work_id -> idle'; exit 1; fi"]

    // ---------- classify (judgment AGENT; read-only; ONLY classifies+routes) --
    classify [class="coding", permissions="read-only",
              label="bc-router classify", prompt_file="nodes/bc-router.md",
              prompt="You are the classify step ONLY. The inbox message was ALREADY read upstream by the native `armed` node; it is in your context. Do EXACTLY ONE thing: classify its message_type via the 4-row bc-router table (load nodes/bc-router.md). You MUST NOT re-read or consume the inbox, MUST NOT write code or bd issues, MUST NOT run git/push, MUST NOT run bc-emit or shop-msg respond. Emit ONLY your routing directive: end with {\"preferred_next_label\": \"scenario\"} for assign_scenarios OR non-empty request_bugfix (reviewer emits); {\"preferred_next_label\": \"flat\"} for request_maintenance OR empty request_bugfix (implementer emits). If you cannot classify, emit NO directive (fails closed to emit_blk)."]

    // ---------- scenario path (reviewer is SOLE work_done emitter) ----------
    suff     [class="coding", permissions="read-only",
              label="bc-sufficiency-check", prompt_file="nodes/bc-sufficiency-check.md",
              prompt="You are the sufficiency step ONLY. Judge the message binary proceed|clarify per the per-message-type sufficiency criteria (load nodes/bc-sufficiency-check.md). You MUST NOT dispatch, implement, plan, write code/bd, run git/push, or run bc-emit/shop-msg respond. Emit ONLY your routing directive: {\"preferred_next_label\": \"proceed\"} if sufficient, or {\"preferred_next_label\": \"clarify\"} (naming the gap) if insufficient. Otherwise emit NO directive (fails closed to emit_blk)."]
    worktree [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true,
              label="using-git-worktrees", prompt_file="nodes/using-git-worktrees.md",
              script="set -e; git worktree add \"../wt-${WORK_ID}\" -b \"work/${WORK_ID}\" origin/main"]
    plan     [class="coding", permissions="read-write",
              label="writing-plans-bdd", prompt_file="nodes/writing-plans-bdd.md",
              prompt="You are the planning step ONLY. Decompose the assigned scenario(s) into a bd sub-issue DAG: one RED + one GREEN sub-issue per behavior, bd dep edges encoding order (load nodes/writing-plans-bdd.md). You MAY create bd issues ONLY; you MUST NOT write source/test code, run git commit/push, integrate, or run bc-emit/shop-msg respond. Emit ONLY: end with {\"preferred_next_label\": \"ok\"} on success; if you cannot decompose emit NO directive (fails closed to emit_blk)."]
    impl     [class="coding", permissions="read-write", parallel=true,
              label="bc-implementer (parallel fan-out)", prompt_file="nodes/subagent-driven-development.md",
              prompt="You are the implementation step ONLY. subagent-driven-development: `bd ready` -> fan out unblocked sub-issues in PARALLEL to bc-implementer subagents; each runs test-driven-development RED->GREEN->REFACTOR IN THE WORKTREE `../wt-${WORK_ID}` and recomputes @scenario_hash via `scenarios hash` (block-only, ADR-019) == on-disk tag (load nodes/subagent-driven-development.md, +test-driven-development.md, +bc-implementer.md). You MUST NOT push to origin/main (the native `integ` node does that), MUST NOT run bc-emit, MUST NOT run shop-msg respond, MUST NOT consume the inbox. Emit ONLY: {\"preferred_next_label\": \"ok\"} if ALL sub-issues are GREEN; on any failure emit NO directive (fails closed to emit_blk)."]
    redgate  [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true,
              label="RED-before-GREEN inter-layer gate", prompt_file="nodes/subagent-driven-development.md",
              script="cd \"../wt-${WORK_ID}\" || exit 1; red=$(git log --oneline --reverse | grep -n 'test(red)' | head -1 | cut -d: -f1); green=$(git log --oneline --reverse | grep -n 'feat(green)' | head -1 | cut -d: -f1); [ -n \"$red\" ] && [ -n \"$green\" ] && [ \"$red\" -lt \"$green\" ]"]
    integ    [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=2,
              label="integrating-to-main", prompt_file="nodes/integrating-to-main.md",
              script="set -e; cd \"../wt-${WORK_ID}\"; git fetch origin; git rebase origin/main; git push origin \"HEAD:main\""]
    review   [class="review", permissions="read-write",
              label="bc-reviewer / bc-review", prompt_file="nodes/bc-review.md",
              prompt="You are the adversarial REVIEW step ONLY. Re-run the BDD suite; probe faithful realization; probe step defs (broad regex / swallowed exceptions / state leakage); verify test(red) precedes feat(green) (load nodes/bc-review.md, +bc-reviewer.md). You MUST NOT modify source/tests, MUST NOT push or integrate, MUST NOT run bc-emit, MUST NOT run shop-msg respond, MUST NOT consume the inbox. Emit ONLY your routing directive: {\"preferred_next_label\": \"signoff\"} | {\"preferred_next_label\": \"scenario_gap\"} | {\"preferred_next_label\": \"impl_gap\"}. If you cannot conclude, emit NO directive (fails closed to emit_blk)."]
    // wdg_r/emit_r run IN THE INTEGRATED WORKTREE (../wt-$WORK_ID), NOT the stale
    // sandbox cwd -- the deliverable (the impl'd + integrated scenario) lives there.
    // Slice-5 RERUN fix: the old scripts ran in /root/sandbox and called bare
    // `scenarios hash` (which reads a scenario block from STDIN; with no pipe it
    // hashes the EMPTY string -> e3b0c442... -> bc-emit C3 [on-disk recompute (subset)
    // payload] rejected). Correct: cd to the worktree, and pass EVERY on-disk
    // @scenario_hash as a repeatable --scenario-hash so C3's recompute is a subset.
    wdg_r    [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true,
              label="work-done-gate (3 checks)", prompt_file="nodes/work-done-gate.md",
              script="cd \"../wt-${WORK_ID}\" || exit 1; git fetch origin >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1; [ -z \"$(git status --porcelain -uall features src tests 2>/dev/null)\" ] || exit 1; git log origin/main -E --grep \"(^|[^0-9a-zA-Z-])${WORK_ID}([^0-9a-zA-Z-]|$)\" | grep -q . || exit 1; grep -rqE '@scenario_hash:[0-9a-f]+' features/ || exit 1"]
    emit_r   [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=2,
              label="reviewer emits work_done -- SOLE EMITTER", prompt_file="nodes/work-done-gate.md",
              script="cd \"../wt-${WORK_ID}\" || exit 1; SH=$(grep -rhoE '@scenario_hash:[0-9a-f]+' features/ | sed 's/@scenario_hash:/--scenario-hash /' | tr '\n' ' '); bc-emit work-done --bc \"$BC_NAME\" --work-id \"$WORK_ID\" $SH --status complete --summary 'reviewer signoff; work-done-gate re-run green; RED-before-GREEN verified; probes considered+dismissed'"]

    // ---------- flat path (implementer is the emitter; no reviewer) --------
    impl_f   [class="coding", permissions="read-write",
              label="bc-implementer (maintenance / empty bugfix)", prompt_file="nodes/bc-implementer.md",
              prompt="You are the FLAT implementation step ONLY (no planning, no reviewer). Make the flat change for request_maintenance or empty request_bugfix (load nodes/bc-implementer.md). You MUST NOT push to origin/main (the native emit path handles integration on the flat lane), MUST NOT run bc-emit, MUST NOT run shop-msg respond, MUST NOT consume the inbox. Emit ONLY: {\"preferred_next_label\": \"ok\"} on change made; {\"preferred_next_label\": \"clarify\"} on insufficient intake; on failure emit NO directive (fails closed to emit_blk)."]
    wdg_f    [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true,
              label="work-done-gate (3 checks)", prompt_file="nodes/work-done-gate.md",
              script="git fetch origin >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1; [ -z \"$(git status --porcelain -uall features src tests 2>/dev/null)\" ] || exit 1; git log origin/main -E --grep \"(^|[^0-9a-zA-Z-])${WORK_ID}([^0-9a-zA-Z-]|$)\" | grep -q . || exit 1; scenarios hash >/dev/null 2>&1 || exit 1"]
    emit_f   [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=2,
              label="implementer emits work_done", prompt_file="nodes/work-done-gate.md",
              script="bc-emit work-done --bc \"$BC_NAME\" --work-id \"$WORK_ID\" --status complete --summary 'flat change (maintenance/empty-bugfix) landed; work-done-gate re-run green'"]

    // ---------- shared report emitters (NATIVE script nodes; templated env) ---
    emit_clar [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=2,
               label="emit clarify",
               script="shop-msg respond clarify --bc \"$BC_NAME\" --work-id \"$WORK_ID\" --question 'insufficient intake or scenario gap surfaced by the loop; see run context'"]
    emit_blk  [shape=parallelogram, deterministic=true, retry=2,
               label="emit work_done BLOCKED (named evidence)",
               script="shop-msg respond work_done --bc \"$BC_NAME\" --work-id \"$WORK_ID\" --status blocked --summary 'a deliverable-side gate or step failed (see run context); reporting blocked, never a silent complete'"]

    // =======================================================================
    // EDGES -- PROVEN-SAFE fail-closed pattern:
    //   single-success node:  node -> success (UNCONDITIONAL, no label)
    //                         node -> failsafe [condition="outcome=failed"]
    //   multi-branch AGENT:   labelled branches (directive-routed) PLUS one
    //                         condition="outcome=failed" catch.
    //   NATIVE 2-way fork:    uncond success edge + condition="outcome=failed"
    //                         edge (native nodes CANNOT emit a routing directive).
    // `halt` is a native exit-1 SINK (run=FAILED). `reported` -> `done`.
    // =======================================================================
    start -> prime

    // --- session start (all NATIVE: uncond success + condition catch) -------
    prime  -> health                              // success (uncond)
    prime  -> halt  [condition="outcome=failed"]  // shop-msg/bd unreachable -> HALT

    health -> arm                                 // success (uncond)
    health -> halt  [condition="outcome=failed"]  // unhealthy -> role loop never begins

    arm    -> armed                               // drain OK (reachable)
    arm    -> halt  [condition="outcome=failed"]  // shop-msg error -> HALT

    // armed: NATIVE 2-way (message present vs empty idle) -- no directive needed
    armed  -> classify                            // message present -> classify
    armed  -> done   [condition="outcome=failed"] // empty inbox -> legitimate idle SUCCEEDED

    // --- classify: multi-branch AGENT (scenario|flat) + failure catch -------
    classify -> suff   [label="scenario"]         // assign_scenarios | non-empty request_bugfix
    classify -> impl_f [label="flat"]             // request_maintenance | empty request_bugfix
    classify -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"] // stage error -> report blocked

    // --- scenario path ---
    // suff: multi-branch AGENT (proceed|clarify) + failure catch
    suff -> worktree   [label="proceed"]
    suff -> emit_clar  [label="clarify"]          // insufficient -> clarify, STOP
    suff -> emit_blk   [condition="outcome=failed"]

    worktree -> plan                              // NATIVE success (uncond)
    worktree -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"]

    plan -> impl                                  // AGENT single-success (uncond)
    plan -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"]

    impl -> redgate                               // AGENT success; internal parallel fan-out converges here
    impl -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"]

    redgate -> integ                              // NATIVE success (uncond)
    redgate -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"] // RED not before GREEN -> BLOCK, must NOT integrate

    integ -> review                               // NATIVE success (uncond)
    integ -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"]

    // review: multi-branch AGENT (signoff|scenario_gap|impl_gap) + stage-error catch
    review -> wdg_r     [label="signoff"]
    review -> emit_clar [label="scenario_gap"]    // gap in scenario -> clarify to lead
    review -> emit_blk  [label="impl_gap"]        // implementation gap -> work_done blocked
    review -> halt      [condition="outcome=failed"] // genuine review stage error -> HALT

    wdg_r -> emit_r                               // NATIVE success (uncond)
    wdg_r -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"] // any of C1/C2/C3 fails -> BLOCKED, never complete

    emit_r -> done                                // NATIVE success (uncond)
    emit_r -> halt [condition="outcome=failed"]   // UNIQUE collision / retry-exhausted -> HALT

    // --- flat path ---
    // impl_f: multi-branch AGENT (ok|clarify) + failure catch
    impl_f -> wdg_f     [label="ok"]
    impl_f -> emit_clar [label="clarify"]         // failed sufficiency on flat path -> clarify directly
    impl_f -> emit_blk  [condition="outcome=failed"]

    wdg_f -> emit_f                               // NATIVE success (uncond)
    wdg_f -> emit_blk [condition="outcome=failed"]

    emit_f -> done                                // NATIVE success (uncond)
    emit_f -> halt [condition="outcome=failed"]

    // --- report emitters converge on REPORTED (a correct non-failure end) ---
    emit_clar -> reported                         // NATIVE success (uncond)
    emit_clar -> halt [condition="outcome=failed"] // send failed -> HALT
    emit_blk  -> reported                          // NATIVE success (uncond)
    emit_blk  -> halt [condition="outcome=failed"] // send failed -> HALT

    // --- reported passthrough to the single SUCCEEDED terminal ---
    reported -> done
}
